x4freetext: The 5.3 MeV s-wave resonance
Chemical form - MoO3, evaporation technique - radiant
heat or electron gun, target thickness - 210 mu-g/cm2.
This resonance was analysed under the least-squares
criterion using code SNOW.
The data are average values over the 3 angles.
The compiled total width was calculated as sum of the
proton partial width for elastic scattering and the
spreading width, which are presented in Tab.2.
No information on uncertainties.
